Define transforms¶

In [429]:
def raw(X):
    return X

def log(X):
    return X.log1p()

def binary(X):
    return (X>0).astype(float)

def chop(pct): # round down to the indicated percentile
    def f(X):
        thresh = np.percentile(X.data, pct)
        return X.minimum(thresh)
    return f
In [430]:
transforms = {'raw': raw, 'log': log, 'binary': binary, 'chop_95':chop(95), 'chop_99':chop(99)}

for d in datasets.values():
    for name, trans in transforms.items():
        X_trans = trans(d.X)
        U,s,Vt = pca(X_trans, k=N_PCS)
        d.obsm['pca_{}'.format(name)] = U*s
        sc.pp.neighbors(d, use_rep='pca_{}'.format(name), key_added=name)

Assess similarity of nearest-neighbor graphs¶

In [433]:
for d in datasets.values():
    
    
    sim_df = pd.DataFrame({x:[1.]*len(transforms) for x in sorted(transforms.keys())})
    sim_df.index = sorted(transforms.keys())
    
    for t1 in sorted(transforms.keys()):
        for t2 in sorted(transforms.keys()):
            if t1 < t2:
                g1 = (d.obsp['{}_connectivities'.format(t1)]>0)
                g2 = (d.obsp['{}_connectivities'.format(t2)]>0)
                
                sim = (g1.multiply(g2).nnz)/float((g1+g2).nnz)
                sim_df[t1][t2] = sim
                sim_df[t2][t1] = sim
    d.uns['neighbor_sims'] = sim_df

Assess clustering similarity¶

Are the clusterings produced by log/binary/raw data transformations similar to each other, according to AMI?

In [454]:
transforms.keys()
Out[454]:
dict_keys(['raw', 'log', 'binary', 'chop_95', 'chop_99'])
In [455]:
for d in datasets.values():

    sim_df = pd.DataFrame({x:[1.]*len(transforms.keys()) for x in sorted(transforms.keys())})
    sim_df.index = sorted(transforms.keys())
    
    for t1 in transforms.keys():
        for t2 in transforms.keys():
            if t1 < t2:
                sim_df[t1][t2] = adjusted_rand_score(d.obs['louvain_{}'.format(t1)].values, d.obs['louvain_{}'.format(t2)].values)
                sim_df[t2][t1] = adjusted_rand_score(d.obs['louvain_{}'.format(t2)].values, d.obs['louvain_{}'.format(t1)].values)
    d.uns['interclust_amis'] = sim_df
